Hi everyone,
I recently installed the 1.6.2 version of the plugins downloading the .zip file on my Linux Ubuntu Studio 22.04 distribution.
I'm using them on my Reaper 6.66.

It seems to me that, inside the zip package, some plugin file is missing. Talking about:

- `SPARTA - DirASS`;
- `SPARTA - PowerMap`;
- `SPARTA - SLDoA`;
- `HO-DirAC - Decoder`;
- `HO-DirAC - upmixer`;

Even if they are documented on the [reference page](https://leomccormack.github.io/sparta-site/docs/plugins/overview/).

On the other hand, I noticed that among the available plugins there is also the "`SPARTA PitchShifter`", which is not listed on the documentation page.

Maybe I should download the missing plugins in another mode?
Thank you so much for your support

I just tested panner in reaper with some automation and noticed a few quirks.

The puck doesn't move to follow the values, even though the values change at the side.

Also write automation by using puck doesn't work. It continues to read. So can only hand draw automation.

Also the parameter naming seems off by one with first name appearing twice. See screenshot.

<img width="330" alt="screen shot 2019-01-06 at 15 05 03" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/837315/50737903-d453c500-11c5-11e9-8c2d-055dfcc6ac61.png">

Looking at the code for parameter naming it seems odd to me.

Why is uneven or zero used? Is parameter 0 a special case?

```
const String PluginProcessor::getParameterName (int index)
{
    if (index % 2 || index == 0)
        return TRANS("Azim_") + String(index/2);
    else
        return TRANS("Elev_") + String((index-1)/2);
}

const String PluginProcessor::getParameterText(int index)
{
    if (index % 2 || index == 0)
        return String(panner_getSourceAzi_deg(hPan, index/2));
    else
        return String(panner_getSourceElev_deg(hPan, (index-1)/2));
}

```
